  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is average cost per couple to travel Bhutan from AHMEDABAD?",
  "response": "To estimate the average cost per couple for traveling to Bhutan from Ahmedabad, we need to consider several factors including airfare, visa fees, daily tariffs in Bhutan, and other expenses. Here's a breakdown:\n\n1. **Flight from Ahmedabad to Paro (Bhutan):**\n   - Round-trip flights can vary greatly in price, but a reasonable estimate might be around INR 30,000 to INR 50,000 per person.\n   - For a couple, this would be INR 60,000 to INR 100,000.\n\n2. **Visa Fees:**\n   - The visa fee for Bhutan is approximately USD 40 per person.\n   - For a couple, this would be around USD 80 (approximately INR 6,640).\n\n3. **Sustainable Development Fee (SDF) in Bhutan:**\n   - Bhutan has a daily SDF of USD 200 per person per night (effective from September 2023).\n   - If you plan to stay for 7 days, the total SDF for one person would be USD 1,400.\n   - For a couple, this would be USD 2,800 (approximately INR 232,400).\n\n4. **Accommodation and Meals:**\n   - The minimum daily package rate in Bhutan includes accommodation, all meals, a guide, and transportation within Bhutan.\n   - This package rate is approximately USD 250 per person per day (on top of the SDF).\n   - For 7 days, this would be USD 1,750 per person.\n   - For a couple, this would be USD 3,500 (approximately INR 290,500).\n\n5. **Other Expenses:**\n   - Miscellaneous expenses like souvenirs, tips, and personal expenses can add up.\n   - A reasonable estimate might be around INR 20,000 for a couple.\n\n**Total Estimated Cost for a 7-day trip per couple:**\n- Flights: INR 60,000 - INR 100,000\n- Visa Fees: INR 6,640\n- SDF: INR 232,400\n- Package Rate: INR 290,500\n- Other Expenses: INR 20,000\n\n**Total: INR 609,540 to INR 649,540**\n\nPlease note that these are rough estimates and actual costs can vary based on the time of year, specific travel agencies, and personal spending habits. It's always a good idea to get quotes from travel agencies specializing in Bhutan tours for more accurate figures.",
